<1ST_LINE>r a AM-ToyPistol     07-19 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Toy Pistol,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Realizes Pistol Is Fake, Hits Robber With Stapler</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When dry cleaning shop owner Janet Castiglione
realized the robber shooting at the ceiling Monday was firing a
harmless cap gun, she got in a few licks of her own.
   She hit the man repeatedly on the face and shoulders with a
stapler before he fled.
   ``I was fed up,'' said Ms. Castiglione, 48, who has been robbed
before. ``And when he shot the gun and I realized it was a cap gun,
I became very angry.''
   The man brandishing what looked like a real revolver entered the
R.J. Valet Cleaners in downtown Pittsburgh shortly after noon. Ms.
Castiglione said the man demanded money and began firing the cap
gun.
   She pounded on him with the stapler, but when she slammed the
cash register shut, some bills flew into the air. The man grabbed
between $30 and $50 and fled, escaping in a car, she said.
</TEXT>
