<HEAD>Schedule of Coverage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a schedule of network coverage of the
Democratic National Convention for tonight, all times EDT:
   ABC, CBS and NBC plan live, prime-time coverage of the
convention from 9-11 p.m., with adjustments as news developments
warrant.
   C-SPAN is carrying live, uninterrupted coverage of the entire
convention session, beginning Tuesday at 4:30 p.m.
   CNN also will cover the entire session, interspersed with
commentary and interviews.
   All the network morning shows are originating from Atlanta, as
are PBS' ``MacNeil-Lehrer NewsHour,'' ABC's ``Nightline'' and CBS'
``Nightwatch.''
   Convention events scheduled to take place during the networks'
prime-time coverage Tuesday include a speech by U.S. Sen. Edward
Kennedy, presentation of platform issues and Jesse Jackson's
long-anticipated speech to the delegates.
