<HEAD>Communications Workers Ratify AP Contract</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Communications Department employees of The
Associated Press ratified a new two-year contract, Communications
Workers of America Local 1314 President James Peecook said today.
   Tentative agreement was reached in New York on June 17 after
seven weeks of bargaining.
   Peecook said the new agreement was adopted by a vote of 118-74,
and that negotiated increases would be retroactive to the May 19
expiration date of the old contract.
   CWA Local 1314 has over 300 members who operate, maintain and
install all equipment used by the AP to send and receive stories
and in its other communications endeavors.
