<HEAD>Peasant With Grenades Dies Trying To Rob Bank</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A peasant armed with grenades and dynamite tried
to hold up a bank but a cashier and a customer threw the grenades
back, fatally wounding him, an official report said Tuesday.
   The People's Daily said Zhang Yongsheng walked into a branch of
the China Agriculture Bank in central China's Henan province July 8
carrying three grenades and seven sticks of dynamite.
   A cashier, Jing Chunling, and a customer, Wang Aixia, pushed him
back out the door, the paper said.
   Zhang then pulled the pin out of one grenade and threw it into
the bank. Ms. Jing threw it back outside, where it exploded, the
report said.
   When Zhang threw the two other grenades inside, Wang threw one
back and kicked the other into an adjoining room. Zhang was fatally
wounded by one explosion, dying half an hour later.
   Wang, Ms. Jing and a second cashier were wounded when the third
grenade exploded inside the bank, but the paper said they were out
of danger.
