   ELMSFORD, N.Y. (AP ) _ A man foiled a holdup at a service
station by tossing a plate of spaghetti at a would-be robber,
police said Tuesday.
   The man was shot by the bandits and was hospitalized in stable
condition.ervice station attendant was not hurt.
   Witnesses said Mann sat at the diner counter with napkins and
coffee filters pressed against his side to contain the bleeding
until the ambulance arrived. Mann, who was staying with friends in
Elmsford, was taken to Westchester County Medical Center in
Valhalla.
