<HEAD>California Woman In Good Condition After 150-Foot Fall into Creek</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALEM, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman was in good condition Tuesday after
she fell 150 feet into a creek below a waterfall, authorities said.
   Maureen Elizabeth Johnson, 34, of Laytonville, Calif., lost her
footing and fell into a creek below Koosah Falls at at the
headwaters of the McKenzie River, according to Linn County Sheriff
Art Martinak.
   Johnson pulled herself out of the creek and waited while her
husband, Charles, used a rope to climb down the cliff to help her
while rescuers were summoned, Martinak said.
