<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Britain-PrisonRiot     07-19 0182</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Prison Riot,0186</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Inmates Riot At Scottish Prison; One Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AIRDRIE, Scotland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 80 inmates rampaged through
two sections of a detention center Tuesday in a riot that left at
least one prisoner injured.
   About 40 police in riot gear stood by late Tuesday as other
officers negotiated with the prisoners by telephone. The inmates'
demands were not immediately clear.
   The uprising at Longriggend remand center, which holds suspects
awaiting trial, broke out when two inmates began fighting after
lunch, the domestic news agency Press Association reported.
   The center outside Glasgow, Scotland's largest city, houses
about 240 inmates.
   At one time, more than 80 inmates climbed a roof, tore off tiles
and threw them at prison staff. The chapel also was damaged.
   One of the inmates fell from the roof and was hospitalized with
broken wrists and a knee injury.
   Several inmates surrendered, but about 50 prisoners _ some
wearing hoods to conceal their identity _ continued to taunt police
with chants, Press Association said. Some inmates later left the
roof and barricaded themselves inside a cell block.
</TEXT>
