<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices headed lower today as investors
remained apathetic toward equities in a market awash in mixed
signals.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off 14.76 points at
2,103.13 by midday.
   Declining issues outnumbered advances by almost 2 to 1 in
nationwide trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed stocks, with
469 up, 801 down and 524 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 69.09 million shares as of noon
on Wall Street.
   The Dow average moved up about 2 points in the first half hour
of trading but then eased back as the session wore on despite
continued reports of higher corporate earnings for the second
quarter.
   ``The primary problem is the mood of the market,'' said Alfred
Goldman, a vice president at A.G. Edwards & Sons Inc. in St. Louis.
``I'm very disappointed with today's action. There's a worldwide
malaise about owning equities.''
   Goldman noted that despite relatively favorable fundamentals
such as lower interest rates and higher corporate earnings, ``the
vast majority of investors are in a very apathetic mood ... they're
not coming to the equities trough.''
   Earlier in Tokyo, the key Nikkei 225-share index plummeted more
than 500 points to its lowest level this year. Some traders were
surprised that the plunge in Tokyo did not take a greater toll on
the U.S. stock market.
   Hildegarde Zagorski, a second vice president at Prudential-Bache
Securities Inc., attributed the decline in Japan to inflation fears
sparked by higher oil prices, which rose on Monday following
reports that Iran had acceded to a United Nations resolution
calling for a cease-fire in its war against Iraq.
   But reports that Iran downed three Iraqi jets today cast a veil
of confusion over prospects for a cease-fire.
   Among actively traded issues, IBM was off ~ at 124\; Union
Carbide was down | at 24|; Tandem was off 1 at 18, and Ford was up
] at 51~.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
0.78 to 152.05. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was off 0.75 at 308.33.
