<HEAD>Japanese Auto Parts Maker To Set Up Plant In U.S.</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf pvs, PK USA will ... to CORRECT name of company
to Kogyo sted Kyogo. Picks up 4th graf pvs, The plant ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A major Japanese auto parts manufacturer announced
Tuesday it will set up a new plant in the United States to
manufacture and sell auto parts to domestic and Japanese car makers
in the United States.
   Press Kogyo, Co., based in southwestern Kawasaki, said PK USA
will be located in Shelbyville, Ind.
   PK USA will be owned 75 percent by Press Kogyo and the remaining
25 percent by Mitsui and Co., a Japanese trading company, company
spokesman Mitsuru Kataoka said.
   The plant, which will begin operating by the end of 1989, will
hire about 155 employees, the spokesman said.
   The manufactured car parts will include metal and plastic parts
for use in passenger cars and trucks, he said.
</TEXT>
