<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Drugs     07-19 0401</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Drugs,0412</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Drug Manufacturers Report Higher Second Quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   The nation's leading drug manufacturers reported double-digit
increases in both profits and worldwide sales of their health-care
products for the second quarter.
   Bristol-Myers Co., American Home Products Corp., Eli Lilly & Co.
and Upjohn Co. reported gains in both domestic and overseas
operations.
   Bristol-Myers, based in New York, reported net income of $190.5
million, or 66 cents a share, up 18 percent from $161.5 million, or
56 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $1.46 billion, up 11
percent from $1.31 billion in the second quarter of 1987.
   For the first half, Bristol-Myers reported net earnings of
$401.13 million, or $1.39 a share, on revenue of $2.98 billion,
compared with net income of $335.39 million, or $1.17 a share, on
revenue of $2.66 billion in the first six months of 1987.
   American Home Products, also based in New York, reported net
income of $215.8 million, or $1.48 a share, up 10 percent from
$195.9 million, or $1.33 a share in the year ago period. Revenue
totaled $1.37 billion, up 12 percent from $1.23 billion a year ago.
   For the first six months, American Home reported net income of
$452.9 million, or $3.10 a share on revenue of $2.78 billion. In
the first half of 1987, net income totaled $412.3 million, or $2.78
a share, on revenue of $2.52 billion.
   Indianapolis-based Lilly reported second-quarter net income of
$180.7 million, or $1.27, up 21 percent from $150.3 million, or
$1.03 a share a year ago. Sales for the quarter totaled $1.01
billion, up 10 percent from $925.9 million last year.
   For the first six months, Lilly reported net income of $413.9
million, or $2.89 a share, on sales of $2.09 billion. In the
previous year, the company reported earnings of $355.5 million, or
$2.42 a share, on revenue of $1.89 billion.
   At Kalamazoo, Mich.-based Upjohn, second quarter earnings rose
12 percent to $87.8 million, or 47 cents a share, from $78.6
million, or 42 cents a share a year ago. Revenue totaled $721.6
million, up 10 percent from $655.5 million in the second quarter of
1987.
   Earnings for the first six months of the year reached $183.2
million, or 98 cents a share, on sales of $1.38 billion, up from
$159.5 million, or 85 cents a share, on sales of $1.26 billion in
the first half of 1987.
</TEXT>
