<HEAD>Chrysler Announces Price Of Eagle Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Motors Corp. said Tuesday
its two Eagle Summit subcompact model cars will have suggested
retail prices of $9,084 and $10,066.
   Chrysler said the 1989 four-door Summit DL model will have the
lower price and the four-door Summit LX the higher. Prices were
effective with shipments that began in late June.
   The Summit, built by Mitsubishi, is the third vehicle to carry
the Eagle name. The others are the Eagle Premier, an intermediate
sedan, and the Eagle Medallion sedan and station wagon.
